        Official Singles Chart on 14/4/2017

        14 April 2017 - 20 April 2017

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always…
        - ‘Shape Of You’ by Ed Sheeran climbs back to the top this week, giving it a total of 14 non-consecutive weeks at #1. The last song to make a return to #1 was ‘Love Yourself’ by Justin Bieber last January.
        - ‘Sign Of The Times’ by Harry Styles falls 1-4 following last week’s debut. Interestingly, also previously from 1D, ‘Pillowtalk’ by ZAYN was the most recent song to only spend one week at #1.
        - It’s been a very close & exciting race for the top spot #1 all week. Back on Tuesday, just under 5,000 sales separated the songs at #1 & #4.
        - ‘Symphony’ by Clean Bandit ft Zara Larsson is #1 on the UK airplay chart for a third consecutive week. I predict that this will be at the top of the overall chart in the next week or two.
        - Kendrick Lamar’s album had a big impact on the Official Charts this week, meaning that five tracks from it appear inside the Top 40 today. The album may not be his best, but is still definitely among the best rap music there has been in past few months. Best Songs: ‘Humble’, ‘Loyalty’ & ‘DNA’. Worst Songs: ‘God’. Rating: 8/10.
        - Elsewhere, Lady Gaga debuts at #23 with ‘The Cure’. While I was a big fan of her last album, I’m very pleased to see that she’s going back to the dance-pop that she released at the start of the decade. I still prefer her biggest hits like ‘Born This Way’ for example, but this comes close! It’s also got a good message to go with it as well & while the vocal range here isn’t as big as many of her previous songs, she has still got an impressive voice! I would even say it’s the best new entry of the week across the Top 100.
        - Also, ‘Did You See’ by J Hus also reaches the Top 40 by advancing 41-34 today. Overall, it’s not bad; I love the reggae rhythm to this & while tropical beats have been used far too much on hit songs this year, I think it works very well here. He does sound a bit boring at parts, but this song still grew on me a lot. Nice to see it keep rising!
        - The two notable climbers in this week’s Top 40 are ‘Swalla’ by Jason Derulo ft Nicki Minaj & Ty Dolla $ign (24-15) & ‘Humble’ by Kendrick Lamar (31-6). The latter marks Kendrick’s first Top 10 in the UK as a lead artist.
        - On the albums chart, Ed Sheeran remains at #1 for seven weeks in a row. The rest of the Top 5 is: Kendrick Lamar (debuts at #2), Rag’n’Bone Man (2-3), Drake (stationary at #4) & Take That (stationary at #5).
        - Thanks for reading everyone! Have a good weekend. :)

        "Sign of the Times" by Harry Styles debuts at number 1 this week. It is Styles' first single outside of the boy band One Direction. It was written by Harry Styles, Ryan Nasci, & Mitch Rowland. Jeff Bhasker, Tyler Johnson & Alex Salibian produced the song. Jeff Bhasker has produced several hits during his career, like: "Run This Town" by Jay Z (feat Rihanna & Kanye West); "Runaway" by Kanye West (feat Pusha T); "Just Give Me a Reason" by Pink (feat Nate Ruess); and "Uptown Funk" by Mark Ronson. Harry Styles is scheduled to perform on Saturday Night Live (SNL) tomorrow, April 15th. Next Friday he will give his first solo performance in the UK on BBC's The Graham Norton Show. I was very impressed with this song- it proved to me that Harry Styles is an artist with real depth. Beyoncé originally released the song in 2015, for her seventh wedding anniversary, along with a music video of her performing at a piano and wearing a baseball cap.         My thoughts & observations on the UK charts as always…
        - Harry Styles earns his first solo #1 with ‘Sign Of The Times’, finally putting an end to Ed Sheeran’s 13-week reign with ‘Shape Of You’! It’s also Harry’s 15th Top 10 entry including his appearances as part of One Direction.
        - As for the song itself, I wasn’t expecting this sound from Harry at all, but I’m very impressed by it! It’s a fantastic throwback to early 1970s rock & even comparisons to David Bowie have already been made. Harry’s falsetto is decent, but I love his more powerful vocals & especially the riff that closes out the song (it reminds me a lot of ‘Purple Rain’). I don’t see it staying here for very long, but it definitely deserves to!
        - Despite already being the middle of April, ‘Sign Of The Times’ is only the third #1 single of 2017 so far.
        - ‘Symphony’ by Clean Bandit ft Zara Larsson remains at #1 on airplay for a second week.
        - ‘Places’ by Martin Solveig & Ina Wroldsen also enters the Top 40 today, lifting 42-27. It’s Martin’s sixth appearance in this region & Ina’s first! The latter artist wrote most of the song (which actually samples ‘Waiting For A Star To Fall’ by Boy Meets Girl). I think house music suits Martin’s production better, so I’m happy that he returned to this sound. Also, the encompassing bass followed by vocal chops over a catchy drop make me really enjoy this! It might have took its time reaching the Top 40, but that’s better than never. Good song!
        - Disciples make their third Top 40, as ‘On My Mind’ soars 81-34. You may remember them most from their #2-peaking hit with Calvin Harris, ‘How Deep Is Your Love?’, last summer. I definitely like the vocals throughout the song, although the beat seems a bit generic & does get a bit boring & repetitive after the first couple of minutes. Overall, not a bad dance song, but not a good one either & even though it’ll likely climb the Official Charts in the coming weeks, I don’t see myself coming back to listen to this in the coming months.
        - Elsewhere inside the Top 40, notable climbers are: ‘Green Light’ by Lorde (27-20), ‘Mask Off’ by Future (33-26) & ‘Swalla’ by Jason Derulo ft Nicki Minaj & Ty Dolla $ign (34-24).
        - On the albums chart, ‘÷’ by Ed Sheeran earns a sixth consecutive week at #1. The rest of the Top 5 is: ‘Human’ by Rag’n’Bone Man (stationary at #2), ‘Memories… Do Not Open’ by The Chainsmokers (debuts at #3), ‘More Life’ by Drake (3-4) & ‘Wonderland’ by Take That (4-5).
        - Looking ahead to next week, potential new arrivals to the Top 40 include: ‘Best Behaviour’ by Louisa Johnson, ‘Did You See’ by J Hus & ‘Baby’ by Anton Powers & Pixie Lott.
        - Thanks for reading everyone! I hope you all have a good weekend. :)
